{"id": "EUVD-2024-48867", "enisaUuid": "655895c8-afbc-3839-9dfb-87becc5ba832", "description": "An authentication bypass vulnerability has been identified in Pulpcore when deployed with Gunicorn versions prior to 22.0, due to the puppet-pulpcore configuration. This issue arises from Apache's mod_proxy not properly unsetting headers because of restrictions on underscores in HTTP headers, allowing authentication through a malformed header. This flaw impacts all active Satellite deployments (6.13, 6.14 and 6.15) which are using Pulpcore version 3.0+ and could potentially enable unauthorized users to gain administrative access.", "datePublished": "2024-09-04T13:41:48", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-11T16:12:18", "baseScore": 9.8, "baseScoreVersion": "3.0", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H", "references": ["https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2024:6335", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2024:6336", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2024:6337", "https://access.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2024:8906", "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-7923", "https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=2305718"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-7923"], "assigner": "redhat", "epss": 0.37, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "15fe421c-bace-3a89-8d2b-5095ca094366", "product": {"name": "Red Hat Satellite 6.14 for RHEL 8"}, "product_version": "patch: 1:3.7.0.8-1.el8sat"}, {"id": "a7795e39-f3dd-3032-a6e5-caeb3994ca7b", "product": {"name": "Red Hat Satellite 6.15 for RHEL 8"}, "product_version": "patch: 1:3.9.3.4-1.el8sat"}, {"id": "bc901496-5558-3ec6-b654-ab1af7dbb8b1", "product": {"name": "Red Hat Satellite 6.16 for RHEL 9"}, "product_version": "patch: 1:3.12.0.1-1.el9sat"}, {"id": "f4c31927-842b-3794-8b34-d79de1daa83c", "product": {"name": "Red Hat Satellite 6.16 for RHEL 8"}, "product_version": "patch: 1:3.12.0.1-1.el8sat"}, {"id": "fa8afd7e-24e1-3bd7-aa0c-bdd74aaa47c7", "product": {"name": "Red Hat Satellite 6.13 for RHEL 8"}, "product_version": "patch: 1:3.5.2.8-1